  fat: 67 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 86 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 22 g
  fiber: 13 g
  sodium: 1000 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/loaded-quinoa-bowls-5addf1ecae08b54fc11b20d2
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Place @water{1%cup} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} in a small #pot{}. Bring to a boil, then add @quinoa{1/2%cup}. Lower heat, reduce to a simmer, and cover. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}, then transfer to a large #bowl{}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

Meanwhile, heat @vegetable oil{1/4%cup} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Cut @sweet potato{1}(cut into 1/2-inch cubes). Drain @artichokes{6.5%ounce}, then pat dry with a #paper towel{}. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Cut @demi-baguette{1} into 1-inch cubes. Line a #plate{} with paper towels.

> TIP: Dry the artichokes well to reduce oil splatters when cooking.

Once oil is hot, add sweet potato to pan. Cook until tender and crisped, turning to brown all over, about ~{8-10%minutes}. Remove from pan with a #slotted spoon{} and set aside to drain on your lined plate. Season immediately with @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tsp} (we'll use the rest later) and plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add artichokes to same pan. Cook until crisped, turning to brown all over, about ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove from pan with a slotted spoon and transfer to plate with sweet potato. Season immediately with @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tsp} (we'll use the rest in the next step) and plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Carefully pour out oil in pan, then wipe out any charred bits with a paper towel.

Return same pan to medium-high heat and add @butter{1%tbsp} and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}. Once butter melts, add baguette cubes. Toast, tossing, until golden brown all over, about ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix remaining @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{2%tsp}, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, @olive oil{2%tsp}, and @water{1%tsp}. If thick, add another @water{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff quinoa in bowl with a #fork{}, then add @arugula{2%ounce} and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add half each of the sweet potato, artichokes, tomatoes, croutons, and @feta cheese{1/2%cup} and toss to combine. Divide between #bowls{} for serving, then top with remaining half of the ingredients. Drizzle with dressing.